Usage: add_pg_cover_cell [-help] -cell <string> -inst_prefix <string> [{-location {x y} | -area {x1 y1 x2 y2}}] [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2} [-exclude_macro_placement_area ]]

-help                             # Prints out the command usage
-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}               # specifies the area that PG cover instance
                                  # will be added (box, optional)
-cell <string>                    # specifies the PG cover cell name
                                  # (string, required)
-exclude_macro_placement_area     # specifies PG cover instances will be placed
                                  # in the specified area excluding the area
                                  # where macros are placed. Only use with
                                  # -area specified (bool, optional)
-inst_prefix <string>             # specifies the PG cover cell instance prefix
                                  # name that will be added. Names are of the
                                  # form prefix_<int> (string, required)
-location {x y}                   # specifies the location where only one PG
                                  # cover instance will be added (point, optional)